This is an optional construct to allow the user to create their own pools or not use the pool if they so desire.

To use the pooled allocation it works like so:

``` C++
SharedPtr<WorkItem> item = WorkQueue::GetFreeItem();
// Set Item Variables.
WorkQueue::AddWorkItem(item);
```

WorkItems now take in a SharedPtr to allow tracking and usage of the complete volatile boolean, e.g:

``` c++
                SharedPtr<WorkItem> item(new WorkItem());
                item->workFunction_ = UpdateDrawableGeometriesWork;
                item->aux_ = const_cast<FrameInfo*>(&frame_);
                item->start_ = &(*start);
                item->end_ = &(*end);
                queue->AddWorkItem(item);
```

With the recent changes to Text, the generated Lua API fails to compile on Mingw, with the error "passing 'const Urho3D::Text' as 'this' argument of 'const Urho3D::PODVectorUrho3D::IntVector2& Urho3D::Text::GetCharPositions()' discards qualifiers [-fpermissive]
 const PODVector<IntVector2>& tolua_ret = (const PODVector<IntVector2>&)  self->GetCharPositions();.

And a similar error for GetCharSizes().

The offending lines are in pkgs/UI/Text.pkg, lines 45 and 46:

const PODVector<IntVector2>& GetCharPositions() const;
const PODVector<IntVector2>& GetCharSizes() const;

These function signatures do not match the signatures in Graphics/Text.h. Stripping the trailing const modifiers resolves the issue:

const PODVector<IntVector2>& GetCharPositions();
const PODVector<IntVector2>& GetCharSizes();

Hi,

Since the refactor of pingponging code, RTTs stopped to work when they use a renderpath which needs pingponging (tested with OpenGL, I don't know for DirectX).

For a simple way to reproduce, juste modify RenderToTexture.cpp sample line 198 to append to the render path a postprocess which reads & writes the viewport, for example :

``` cpp
            RenderSurface* surface = renderTexture->GetRenderSurface();
            RenderPath* renderpath = new RenderPath();
            renderpath->Load(GetSubsystem<ResourceCache>()->GetResource<XMLFile>("RenderPaths/Forward.xml"));
            renderpath->Append(GetSubsystem<ResourceCache>()->GetResource<XMLFile>("PostProcess/EdgeFilter.xml"));
            SharedPtr<Viewport> rttViewport(new Viewport(context_, rttScene_, rttCameraNode_->GetComponent<Camera>(), renderpath));
            surface->SetViewport(0, rttViewport);
```

Then launch the sample, the RTT texture will remain black instead of showing rotating boxes.
